    \item Under \textbf{hotspot traffic}, more adaptive algorithms show clear advantages. Planar Adaptive achieves the lowest latency at 176.3 cycles, followed by ROMM at 219.7 cycles, demonstrating that locally-adaptive routing effectively mitigates hotspot congestion. XY reaches 467.6 cycles, and GNNocRoute-PPO (473.4) performs comparably to XY but does not benefit from the adaptive advantage.
\end{itemize}


